metadata.name: 001 // XXIII
metadata.description:
Cheerfully chirping, briskly aflutter  
Animals spiritedly buzzing abound  
Lusciously verdant, ruggedly regal  
Sturdily supporting all life around

Secretly whispering, inaudibly rustling  
Chittering exuberantly nowhere to be found  
Brilliantly blazing, fallen petals of crimson  
Unceremoniously strewn upon the ground

Eerily silent, unmistakably dormant  
Frozen white speckles descend softly inbound  
Unabashedly barren, lifelessly brittle  
Patiently biding without making a sound

Untilâ€¦

Eagerly awaited, excitedly returning  
Slowly but surely from effigy grew  
Freshly sprouted, graciously hosting  
Vibrantly teeming once more with life anew
metadata.Prompt: You can write whatever you want but use at least 23 adverbs or your whole family dies
metadata.Subtext: A story of recovery, renewal and rebirth through the seasons.
